<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Parable&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-A_Marginal_Jew-0">^ <a href="#cite_ref-A_Marginal_Jew_0-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-A_Marginal_Jew_0-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-A_Marginal_Jew_0-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="/wiki/John_P._Meier" title="John P. Meier">John P. Meier</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/A_Marginal_Jew" title="A Marginal Jew" class="mw-redirect">A Marginal Jew</a></i>, volume II, Doubleday, 1994.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Fowler-1">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Fowler_1-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fowler_1-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fowler_1-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="/wiki/Henry_Watson_Fowler" title="Henry Watson Fowler">H.W. Fowler</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Fowler%27s_Modern_English_Usage" title="Fowler's Modern English Usage" class="mw-redirect">Modern English Usage</a></i>, Oxford, Clarendon Press, 1958.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> For parables as extended metaphors, see Amos Wilder, <i>The Language of the Gospel: Early Christian Rhetoric</i> (New York: Harper &amp; Row) 1964; Robert W, Funk, <i>Language, Hermeneutic and Word of God: The Problem of Language in the New Testament and Contemporary Theology</i> (New York: Harper &amp; Row) 1966; Dan O. Via Jr, <i>The Parables: Their Literary and Existential Dimension</i> (Philadelphia: Fortress) 1967; Sallie TeSelle, <i>Speaking in Parables: A Study in Metaphore and Theology</i> (Philadelphia: Fortress) 1975.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Sallie McFague TeSelle, "Parable, Metaphor, and Theology," <i>Journal of the American Academy of Religion</i>, <b>42</b>.4 (December 1974:630-645).</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/George_Fyler_Townsend" title="George Fyler Townsend">George Fyler Townsend</a>, translator's preface to <i><a href="/wiki/Aesop%27s_Fables" title="Aesop's Fables">Aesop's Fables</a></i>, Belford, Clarke &amp; Co., 1887.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Die_Gleichmisreden_Jesu-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Die_Gleichmisreden_Jesu_5-0" title="">^</a></b> Adolf Jülicher, <i>Die Gleichmisreden Jesu</i> (2 vols; Tübingen: Mohr [Siebeck], 1888, 1899).</li>
</ol>
